===Pronunciation===
へいばんしき (heiban-shiki)

'''Accent: 0 ''' ([[平板型]])

===Noun===
[[Category:Japanese nouns|へいばんしき]]
'''平板式''' ([[へいばんしき]], [[heibanshiki]])

#The pitch accent pattern in Japanese where no syllable is accented; i.e., the first syllable has low pitch and all subsequent syllables have high pitch.

====Synonyms====
*[[平板型]]

====Antonyms====
*[[起伏式]]

====Usage notes====
*All accent patterns in Japanese may be described as either 平板式 or 起伏式. While 起伏式 is further divided into [[頭高型]], [[中高型]], and [[尾高型]], there are no subcategories to 平板式. When contrasting with 頭高型, 中高型, or 尾高型, it is customary to use the word 平板型 to avoid the discrepancy of comparing [[型]] with [[式]].

